A Writer in the Storm of Night

Awoken
by words,
the swirling
possibilities
of poems;

There's wonder
in all that
never gets
scribbled
as ideas rage

only catching
the wind
of night's
slumbered
musings:

this storm
of stories;
this lightning,
to thunder
